https://chocolatey.org/install
1. install chocolatey package manager-> run the following command on powershell as administrator mode

Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force; [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072; iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://community.chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))

2. To install kubectl on Windows you can use Chocolatey package manager

choco install kubernetes-cli

3 Test to ensure the version you installed is up-to-date:
 kubectl version --client

4. we create .kube/config  file in userprofile folder this config file is used to get cluster information


5.Now install minkube using choco package manager 

choco install minikube

6. start minikube cluster using the fillowing command

 minikube start

7 check minikube

 docker ps
 


